HEADWORD: Whistlefish
<hw>Whis"tle*fish`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A gossat, or rockling; -- called also <altname>whistler</altname>,
<altname>three-bearded rockling</altname>, <altname>sea loach</altname>,
and <altname>sorghe</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

